    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 17,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge your note
                            of the 6th instant, inclosing copies of the President’s proclamation of
                            the 13th ultimo, fixing March 1, 1895, as the date on which the laws of
                            the United States, therein mentioned and relating to the new regulations
                            for preventing collisions at sea, are to take effect.</p>
                <p>I did not fail to transmit to my Government a copy of that communication,
                            together with copies of the proclamation.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
